317 A-1 League|2016\u201317]]</center>\n| [[KK Cibona|Cibona]]\n| <center>2\u20133</center>\n| style=\"background:#ff9;\"|'''[[KK Cedevita|Cedevita]]'''\n| [[GKK \u0160ibenik|\u0160ibenik]]\n| <center>21\u20135</center>\n|- \n| <center>[[2017\u201318 A-1 League|2017\u201318]]</center>\n| style=\"background:#ff9;\"| '''[[KK Cedevita|Cedevita]]'''\n| <center>3\u20131</center>\n| [[KK Cibona|Cibona]]\n| [[KK Cedevita|Cedevita]]\n| <center>23\u20131</center>\n|-\n| <center>[[2018\u201319 Premijer liga|2018\u201319]]</center>\n| style=\"background:#ff9;\"|'''[[KK Cibona|Cibona]]'''\n| <center>4\u20130</center>\n| [[KK Cedevita|Cedevita]]\n| [[KK Zadar|Zadar]]\n| <center>18\u20134</center>\n|-\n| <center>[[2019\u201320 Hrvatski telekom Premijer liga|2019\u201320]]</center>\n| colspan=5 style=\"background:#eaecef;\"| '''Season canceled''' due to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Croatia|Coronavirus pandemic]]\n|}\n\n===By club===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:50%;\"| Club\n!W\n!L\n!Total\n|-\n| [[KK Cibona|Cibona]]\n| <center>19</center>\n| <center>7</center>\n| <center>'''26'''</center>\n|-\n| [[KK Cedevita|Cedevita]]\n| <center>5</center>\n| <center>3</center>\n| <center>'''8'''</center>\n|-\n| [[KK Zadar|Zadar]]\n| <center>2</center>\n| <center>11</center>\n| <center>'''13'''</center>\n|-\n| [[KK Split|Split]]\n| <center>1</center>\n| <center>6</center>\n| <center>'''7'''</center>\n|-\n| [[KK Zagreb|Zagreb]]\n| <center>1</center>\n| <center>0</center>\n| <center>'''1'''</center>\n|-\n| [[KK Zrinjevac|Zrinjevac]]\n| <center>0</center>\n| <center>1</center>\n| <center>'''1'''</center>\n|}\n\n==Croatian basketball clubs in European and worldwide competitions==\n{{main|Croatian basketball clubs in European and worldwide competitions}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Kre\u0161imir \u0106osi\u0107 Cup]]\n* [[Croatian First Women's Basketball League]]\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.hks-cbf.hr/ Official Website]\n\n{{A-1 Liga}}\n{{A-1 Liga Seasons}}\n{{Croatian basketball clubs in European and worldwide competitions}}\n{{Basketball in Croatia}}\n{{International basketball}}\n{{Men's professional basketball leagues}}\n\n[[Category:Basketball leagues in Croatia]]\n[[Category:A-1 Liga| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the women's competition|A-1 Liga \u017dene}}\n{{Infobox basketball league\n|name           = Hrvatski telekom Premijer liga \n|image          = hrvatskitelekompremijerliga.png \n|pixels         = 300\n|country        = {{CRO}}\n|other countries= \n|confed         = [[FIBA Europe]]\n|founded        = {{Start date and age|1991}}\n|former_names = O\u017eujsko liga<br>A-1 Liga \n|first          = \n|folded         = \n|divisions      = \n|teams          = [[#Current teams|12]]\n|feeds          = \n|promotion      = \n|relegation     = [[Croatian First Basketball League|First League]] \n|levels         = 1\n|domest_cup     =[[Kre\u0161imir \u0106osi\u0107 Cup]] \n|supercup       = \n|overseas_tournament= \n|confed_cup     = \n|champions      =  [[KK Cibona|Cibona]] (19th title)\n|season         = [[2018\u201319 Premijer liga|2018\u201319]]\n|most_champs    =  [[KK Cibona|Cibona]] (19 titles)\n|top_scorer     = \n|tv             = \n|ceo            =  \n|sponsor        = \n|website        = {{URL|http://www.hks-cbf.hr/}}\n|current        = [[2019\u201320 Hrvatski telekom Premijer liga|2019\u201320 season]]\n}}\nThe '''Hrvatski telekom Premijer liga''' ([[English language|English]]: '''Hrvatski telekom Premier League''') is the first tier level men's professional [[basketball]] league in [[Croatia]]. It began in 1991, following the breakup of [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|SFR Yugoslavia]] and therefore the [[Yugoslav First Basketball League|Yugoslav League]], and is organized by the [[Croatian Basketball Federation]].\n\nThe HT Premijer liga, which is played under [[FIBA Europe|FIBA]] rules, currently consists of 12 teams. The most successful club is [[KK Cibona]] with 19 championship titles.\n\n== History ==\nPrior to 1991, clubs from [[SR Croatia|Croatia]] played in the [[First Federal Basketball League|First Federal Yugoslav League]]. From the [[1946 Yugoslav First Basketball League|inaugural season]] in 1946, three Croatian clubs won 15 National Championships in total; [[KK Zadar|Zadar]] (won six titles), [[KK Split|Split]] (six titles), and [[KK Cibona|Cibona]] (three titles).\n\n== Title holders ==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-3}}\n* 1991\u201392 [[KK Cibona|Cibona]]\n* 1992\u201393 [[KK Cibona|Cibona]]\n* 1993\u201394 [[KK Cibona|Cibona]]\n* 1994\u201395 [[KK Cibona|Cibona]]\n* 1995\u201396 [[KK Cibona|Cibona]]\n* 1996\u201397 [[KK Cibona|Cibona]]\n* 1997\u201398 [[KK Cibona|Cibona]]\n* 1998\u201399 [[KK Cibona|Cibona]]\n* 1999\u201300 [[KK Cibona|Cibona]]\n* 2000\u201301 [[KK Cibona|Cibona]]\n* 2001\u201302 [[KK Cibona|Cibona VIP]]\n* 2002\u201303 [[KK Split|Split CO]]\n* 2003\u201304 [[KK Cibona|Cibona VIP]]\n* 2004\u201305 [[KK Zadar|Zadar]]\n* 2005\u201306 [[KK Cibona|Cibona VIP]]\n{{col-3}}\n* 2006\u201307 [[KK Cibona|Cibona VIP]]\n* 2007\u201308 [[KK Zadar|Zadar]]\n* 2008\u201309 [[KK Cibona|Cibona VIP]]\n* 2009\u201310 [[KK Cibona|Cibona VIP]]\n* 2010\u201311 [[KK Zagreb|Zagreb CO]]\n* 2011\u201312 [[KK Cibona|Cibona]]\n* 2012\u201313 [[KK Cibona|Cibona]]\n* 2013\u201314 [[KK Cedevita|Cedevita]]\n* 2014\u201315 [[KK Cedevita|Cedevita]]\n* 2015\u201316 [[KK Cedevita|Cedevita]]\n* 2016\u201317 [[KK Cedevita|Cedevita]]\n* 2017\u201318 [[KK Cedevita|Cedevita]]\n* 2018\u201319 [[KK Cibona|Cibona]]\n* 2019\u201320 ''Season canceled''\n{{col-3}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n== Performance by club ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! width=100|Club\n! width=80|Champions\n! width=600|Winning years\n|-\n| [[KK Cibona|Cibona]]\n| <center>'''19'''</center>\n| 1991\u201392, 1992\u201393, 1993\u201394, 1994\u201395, 1995\u201396, 1996\u201397, 1997\u201398, 1998\u201399, 1999\u201300, 2000\u201301, 2001\u201302, 2003\u201304, 2005\u201306, 2006\u201307, 2008\u201309, 2009\u201310, 2011\u201312