{"title_page": "Po Lam station", "text_new": "{{short description|Hong Kong MTR station}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}}\n{{Use Hong Kong English|date=March 2017}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name                = Po Lam\n| native_name         = \u5bf6\u7433\n| native_name_lang    = zh-Hant\n| symbol_location     = hk\n| symbol              = mtr\n| type                = [[MTR]] [[rapid transit]] station\n| image               = Po Lam Station Exterior 201405.jpg\n| image_caption       = Exterior of Po Lam Station in 2014\n| mlanguage           = {{Infobox Chinese/Chinese|t=\u5bf6\u7433|s=\u5b9d\u7433|l=Treasure fine jade|j=Bou2lam4|y=B\u00f3ulahm|p=B\u01ceol\u00edn}}\n| address             = Mau Yip Road, Po Lam\n| borough             = [[Tseung Kwan O]], [[Sai Kung District]]\n| country             = [[Hong Kong]]\n| coordinates         = {{coord|22.3224|114.258|region:HK|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| elevation           = \n| line                = {{Plainlist|1=\n* {{rcb|MTR|Tseung Kwan O|yes}}\n}}\n| connections         = \n| distance            =\n| structure           = At-grade\n| platform            = 1 (1 [[side platform]])<ref name = layout>{{cite web |title=Po Lam Station Layout |url=http://www.mtr.com.hk/archive/ch/services/layouts/poa.pdf |publisher=[[MTR Corporation]] |format=PDF |accessdate=29 February 2020}}</ref>\n| depth               = \n| levels              = 1<ref name = layout/>\n| architect           = RMJM Hong Kong Ltd.\n| tracks              = 1<ref name = layout/>\n| parking             = \n| bicycle             = \n| opened              = {{Plainlist|1=\n* {{start-date|18 August 2002}} \n}}\n| opening             = \n| closed              = \n| rebuilt             = \n| electrified         = \n| disabled            = yes\n| code                = POA\n| owned               = [[MTR Corporation]]\n| operator            = [[MTR Corporation]]\n| zone                = \n| former              = \n| passengers          = \n| pass_year           = \n| pass_percent        = \n| pass_system         = \n| mpassengers         =\n| last                =  \n| services            = {{Adjacent stations|system=MTR|line=Tseung Kwan O|left=Hang Hau}}\n| map_type            = Hong Kong MTR\n| map_alt             = Hong Kong MTR system map\n| map_caption         = Location within the [[MTR]] system\n| route_map           = {{Routemap\n|inline=1\n|legend=track\n|map=\nd\\utENDEa\\utENDEa\nd\\utSTR+BSr!~c*1\\utSTR\nd\\utSTR+BSr\\utSTR\nd\\utSTR+BSr\\utSTR!~POINTERg@fq~~ ~~ ~~Siding\nd\\utKRWg+l\\utKRWgr\nutSHI2lr~L\\d!~utSHI2lr~R\\lENDE@G\nutSTRg\\utSTRf\\d\nutSTR!~MFADEf\\utSTR!~MFADEf\\d~~ ~~ ~~to {{stl|MTR|Hang Hau}}\n}}\n| map_state           = expanded\n}}\n\n'''Po Lam''' ({{zh|t=\u5bf6\u7433}}) is the northern [[Train station#Terminus|terminus]] [[MTR]] [[List of Hong Kong MTR stations|station]] of the [[Tseung Kwan O line]]. It is located on Mau Yip Road, [[Po Lam]], in the [[New Territories]] of [[Hong Kong]], sandwiched by Phases 1 to 3 of [[Metro City (Hong Kong)|Metro City]]. Built by [[Maeda Corporation]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Maeda Corporation |url=http://asce.webhost.ust.hk/database/contractor/maeda.htm |publisher=[[Hong Kong University of Science and Technology]] |accessdate=29 February 2020}}</ref>, it opened in August 2002. The name of the station is taken from the nearby Po Lam Road North.\n\n== Station layout ==\n{|border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=3\n| rowspan=\"4\" style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray; border-top:solid 1px gray; vertical-align:top;width:50px;\"|'''U1'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border-top:solid 1px gray; border-bottom:solid 1px gray; vertical-align:top;width:100px;\"|Footbridge<br>(Exit A1, B2)\n|style=\"border-top:solid 1px gray; vertical-align:top;width:500px;\"|[[Metro City (Hong Kong)|Metro City Phases 1 and 3]]\n|-\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\"|[[Vending machines]], [[Automated teller machine|ATMs]], MTR Shops\n|-\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\"|Footbridge<br>(Exit A2, B1)\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\"|[[Metro City (Hong Kong)|Metro City Phase 2]], Transport interchange, Footbridges to [[Public housing estates in Tseung Kwan O#Po Lam Estate|Po Lam Estate]], [[Public housing estates in Tseung Kwan O#Po Lam Estate|Yan Ming Court]]\n|-\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\"|Footbridge<br>(Exit B3)\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\"|Footbridges to rooftop garden, [[The Pinnacle, Hong Kong|The Pinnacle]], [[Public_housing estates in Tseung Kwan O#King Lam Estate|King Lam Estate]]<br />[[List of libraries in Hong Kong|Tseung Kwan O Public Library]], Tseung Kwan O Swimming Pool\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray; vertical-align:top;\"|'''G<br>Concourse/<br>Platforms'''\n|Platform <span style=\"color:#{{rcr|MTR|Tseung Kwan O}};\">'''1'''</span>\n| {{rcb|MTR|Tseung Kwan O|yes}} towards [[North Point station|North Point]] or [[LOHAS Park station|LOHAS Park]] <small>([[Hang Hau Station|Hang Hau]])</small> \u2192\n|-\n|style=\"border-top:solid 2px black;border-right:solid 2px black;border-left:solid 2px black;border-bottom:solid 1px gray;text-align:center;\" colspan=2|<small>[[Side platform]], doors will open on the left</small>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray; vertical-align:top;\"|Concourse\n|Exit C, Customer service, MTR Shops\n|-\n|Vending machines\n|-\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\"|[[Octopus card]] promotion machines\n|}\n[[File: MTR TKL Opening Commemoration Plaque.JPG |right|thumb|250px|Commemorative plague for the opening of [[Tseung Kwan O Line]] is at Po Lam station]]\n[[File:Po Lam Station 2013.JPG|thumb|right|250px|The concourse in 2013]]\n[[File:Po Lam MTR Station Exit A.JPG|thumb|right|250px|Exit A in 2006]]\n[[File:Po Lam Station 2013 08 part2.JPG|thumb|right|250px|Exit B in 2013]]\n[[File:Po Lam Station 2014 03 part2.JPG|thumb|right|250px|Exit C in 2014]]\n\nUnlike most [[MTR]] [[train station|stations]] and unique in the [[Tseung Kwan O Line]], the concourse, gates and platform of Po Lam station are on the same level. [[Track (rail transport)|Tracks]] ascend from underground to ground level at the southern end of the station, along [[Public_housing estates in Tseung Kwan O#King Lam Estate|King Lam Estate]]. A park is located on top of the tracks to cover them.\n\n=== Platforms ===\nThere is only one [[side platform]] (Platform 1) from which trains depart, in the same direction as they arrive. Trains, as a result, halt on their way from [[Hang Hau station]] for another train to depart at the station. Trains also stay here for a shorter period before departing than at other MTR [[Train station#Terminus|terminals]]. The single-track design (and the consequent longer train turnback time) limits the maximum train service frequency of the Tseung Kwan O Line.<ref name=layout/><ref>{{cite web|title=Supplementary Information on Tseung Kwan O Extension (Phase II) Service|url=http://www.legco.gov.hk/yr08-09/english/panels/tp/papers/tp0424cb1-2364-1-e.pdf|publisher=[[Legislative Council of Hong Kong|Legislative Council Panel on Transport]]|format=PDF|date=July 2009|accessdate=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nAcross from the platform and north of the point where the tracks merge to one, there is a [[siding (rail)|siding]] that splits from the running line for parking trains. Trains cannot access the platform from the siding, nor can they access the siding from the platform.<ref>{{cite web |title=MTR Track Diagram |url=http://mtr.hk365day.com/Railway/Special/track/MTR_track_diagram_full.pdf |website=mtr.hk365day.com |accessdate=3 March 2020 |format=PDF |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303165205/http://mtr.hk365day.com/Railway/Special/track/MTR_track_diagram_full.pdf |archivedate=3 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Po Lam Station 2017 07 part3.jpg|center|thumb|800px|<center>Platform 1 in July 2017</center>]]\n[[File: Po Lam Station 2017 part2.jpg |center|thumb|800px|<center>The concourse in August 2017</center>]]\n\n== Entrances/exits ==\nThe main exit is on Mau Yip Road, where five pedestrian [[footbridges]] link the station to a public transport interchange, shopping malls and residential buildings. There is direct access to [[Metro City (Hong Kong)|Metro City]] and [[The Pinnacle, Hong Kong|The Pinnacle]] from the concourse. Another footbridge crosses Po Fung Road and leads to [[Public housing estates in Tseung Kwan O#Po Lam Estate|Po Lam Estate]], [[Public housing estates in Tseung Kwan O#Yan Ming Court|Yan Ming Court]] and [[Public housing estates in Tseung Kwan O#Verbena Heights|Verbena Heights]].\n*'''A1''': [[Metro City (Hong Kong)#Shopping centre|Metro City Plaza III]] {{access icon|15px|Wheelchair user access}}\n*'''A2''': [[Metro City (Hong Kong)#Shopping centre|Metro City Plaza II]] {{access icon|15px|Wheelchair user access}}\n*'''B1''': [[Metro City (Hong Kong)#Shopping centre|Metro City Plaza II]]\n*'''B2''': [[Metro City (Hong Kong)#Shopping centre|Metro City Plaza I]]\n*'''B3''': [[Public_housing estates in Tseung Kwan O#King Lam Estate|King Lam Estate]]\n*'''C''': Mau Yip Road {{access icon|15px|Wheelchair user access}}\n\n== Station artwork ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! !!Name!!Artist!!Location!!Completion date\n|-\n|[[File:POA Station art.jpg|200px]]||City of Towers||Kacey Wong||Entrance A1 & B2||August 2002\n|}<ref>{{cite web |title=Art in station architecture: City of Towers |url=http://www.mtr.com.hk/en/customer/community/art_archi_city_of_towers.html |publisher=MTR Corporation |accessdate=6 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Transport connections ==\n=== Minibus routes ===\n<ref name = streetmap>{{cite web |title=Po Lam station street map |url=https://www.mtr.com.hk/archive/en/services/maps/poa.pdf |publisher=MTR Corporation |accessdate=6 March 2020 |format=PDF |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306142158/https://www.mtr.com.hk/archive/en/services/maps/poa.pdf |archivedate=6 March 2020}}</ref>\n* '''10M''' (Exit C): to [[Kwun Tong]]\n* '''11S''' (Exit A2): to [[Choi Hung Estate]] (overnight only)\n* '''12''' (Exit A2): to [[Sai Kung Town|Sai Kung]]\n* '''15''' (Exit A2): to [[Public housing estates in Tseung Kwan O#Hong Sing Garden|Hong Sing Garden]]\n* '''15A''' (Exit C): to [[Hang Hau]] (non-rush hours only)\n* '''15M''' (Exit C): to Hong Sing Garden\n* '''16''' (Exit A2): to [[Po Toi O]]\n* '''17A''' (Excit C): to [[Tseung Kwan O Village]] (morning rush hours only)\n* '''17M''' (Exit C): to [[Public housing estates in Tseung Kwan O#Tsui Lam Estate|Tsui Lam Estate]]\n* '''19S''' (Exit C): to [[Causeway Bay]] (overnight only)\n* '''19S''' (Exit A2): to Hang Hau (overnight only)\n* '''105''' (Exit C): to [[To Kwa Wan]]\n* '''105S''' (Exit C): to [[To Kwa Wan]] (overnight only)\n* '''107''' (Exit C): to [[Haven of Hope Hospital]]\n* '''111''' (Exit A2): to [[San Po Kong]]\n\n=== Bus routes ===\n<ref name = streetmap/>\n* '''91M''' (Exit A2): to [[Diamond Hill station]]\n* '''93A''' (Exit A2): to [[Kwun Tong Ferry Pier]]\n* '''93K''' (Exit B1): to [[Mong Kok East station]]\n* '''98A''' (Exit C): to [[Kwun Tong]]\n* '''98C''' (Exit C): to [[Mei Foo Sun Chuen|Mei Foo]]\n* '''98D''' (Exit C): to [[Tsim Sha Tsui#East Tsim Sha Tsui|Tsim Sha Tsui East]]\n* '''98P''' (Exit C): to Tsim Sha Tsui East (morning rush hours only)\n* '''98S''' (Exit C): to Mei Foo (rush hours on weekdays only)\n* '''290/290A''' (Exit A2): to [[Tsuen Wan West station]]\n* '''293S''' (Exit A2): to Mong Kok East Station (overnight only)\n* '''296M''' (Exit A2): to [[Hang Hau station]]\n* '''297''' (Exit C): to [[Hung Hom]]\n* '''690''' (Exit A2): to [[Exchange Square (Hong Kong)|Exchange Square]], [[Central, Hong Kong|Central]]\n* '''690P''' (Exit A2): to Exchange Square, Central (morning rush hours on weekdays only)\n* '''798''' (Exit A2): to [[Fo Tan]]\n* '''798A''' (Exit A2): to Fo Tan (morning rush hours on weekdays only)\n* '''893''' (Exit A2): to [[Public housing estates in Tseung Kwan O#Hong Sing Garden|Hong Sing Garden]] (on race days only)\n* '''A29''' (Exit A2): to [[Hong Kong International Airport]]\n* '''E22A''' (Exit A2): to [[AsiaWorld-Expo]]\n* '''N293''' (Exit A2): to Mong Kok East Station\n* '''N691''' (exit A2): to [[Hong Kong\u2013Macau Ferry Terminal]], Central\n* '''N29''' (Exit A2): to [[Tung Chung station]]\n* '''NA29''' (Exit A2): to [[Hong Kong International Airport]] (overnight only)\n\n== Future development ==\n{{main|East Kowloon line}}\nThe [[Government of Hong Kong|government]] proposed in the Railway Development Strategy 2014 that East Kowloon Line will connect Po Lam and [[Diamond Hill station|Diamond Hill]] stations, passing through Po Tat, Sau Mau Ping, Shun Tin and Choi Wan stations. It will serve as an alternative route to reach [[Kwun Tong Line]] in case of disruption on the [[Tseung Kwan O Line]], and is expected to open in 2025.<ref>{{cite web |title=Railway Development Strategy 2014 |url=https://www.thb.gov.hk/eng/psp/publications/transport/publications/rds2014.pdf |publisher=[[Transport and Housing Bureau]] |format=PDF |accessdate=6 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Fung |first1=Fanny |last2=Siu |first2=Phila |title=Surprise new MTR line planned for Kwun Tong |url=https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/article/1594877/surprise-new-mtr-line-planned-kwun-tong |accessdate=6 March 2020 |publisher=[[South China Morning Post]] |date=18 September 2014}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{Commons category inline|Po Lam Station}}\n{{Sai Kung District}}\n{{Tseung Kwan O Line navbox}}\n{{East Kowloon Line navbox}}\n\n[[Category:MTR stations in the New Territories]]\n[[Category:Tseung Kwan O line]]\n[[Category:Po Lam]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 2002]]\n[[Category:2002 establishments in Hong Kong]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Hong Kong MTR station}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}}\n{{Use Hong Kong English|date=March 2017}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name                = Po Lam\n| native_name         = \u5bf6\u7433\n| native_name_lang    = zh-Hant\n| symbol_location     = hk\n| symbol              = mtr\n| type                = [[MTR]] [[rapid transit]] station\n| image               = Po Lam Station Exterior 201405.jpg\n| image_caption       = Exterior of Po Lam Station in 2014\n| mlanguage           = {{Infobox Chinese/Chinese|t=\u5bf6\u7433|s=\u5b9d\u7433|l=Treasure fine jade|j=Bou2lam4|y=B\u00f3ulahm|p=B\u01ceol\u00edn}}\n| address             = Mau Yip Road, Po Lam\n| borough             = [[Tseung Kwan O]], [[Sai Kung District]]\n| country             = [[Hong Kong]]\n| coordinates         = {{coord|22.3224|114.258|region:HK|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| elevation           = \n| line                = {{Plainlist|1=\n* {{rcb|MTR|Tseung Kwan O|yes}}\n}}\n| connections         = \n| distance            =\n| structure           = At-grade\n| platform            = 1 (1 [[side platform]])<ref name = layout>{{cite web |title=Po Lam Station Layout |url=http://www.mtr.com.hk/archive/ch/services/layouts/poa.pdf |publisher=[[MTR Corporation]] |format=PDF |accessdate=29 February 2020}}</ref>\n| depth               = \n| levels              = 1<ref name = layout/>\n| architect           = RMJM Hong Kong Ltd.\n| tracks              = 1<ref name = layout/>\n| parking             = \n| bicycle             = \n| opened              = {{Plainlist|1=\n* {{start-date|18 August 2002}} \n}}\n| opening             = \n| closed              = \n| rebuilt             = \n| electrified         = \n| disabled            = yes\n| code                = POA\n| owned               = [[MTR Corporation]]\n| operator            = [[MTR Corporation]]\n| zone                = \n| former              = \n| passengers          = \n| pass_year           = \n| pass_percent        = \n| pass_system         = \n| mpassengers         =\n| last                =  \n| services            = {{Adjacent stations|system=MTR|line=Tseung Kwan O|left=Hang Hau}}\n| map_type            = Hong Kong MTR\n| map_alt             = Hong Kong MTR system map\n| map_caption         = Location within the [[MTR]] system\n| route_map           = {{Routemap\n|inline=1\n|legend=track\n|map=\nd\\utENDEa\\utENDEa\nd\\utSTR+BSr!~c*1\\utSTR\nd\\utSTR+BSr\\utSTR\nd\\utSTR+BSr\\utSTR!~POINTERg@fq~~ ~~ ~~Siding\nd\\utKRWg+l\\utKRWgr\nutSHI2lr~L\\d!~utSHI2lr~R\\lENDE@G\nutSTRg\\utSTRf\\d\nutSTR!~MFADEf\\utSTR!~MFADEf\\d~~ ~~ ~~to {{stl|MTR|Hang Hau}}\n}}\n| map_state           = expanded\n}}\n\n'''Po Lam''' ({{zh|t=\u5bf6\u7433}}) is the northern [[Train station#Terminus|terminus]] [[MTR]] [[List of Hong Kong MTR stations|station]] of the [[Tseung Kwan O line]]. It is located on Mau Yip Road, [[Po Lam]], in the [[New Territories]] of [[Hong Kong]], sandwiched by Phases 1 to 3 of [[Metro City (Hong Kong)|Metro City]]. Built by [[Maeda Corporation]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Maeda Corporation |url=http://asce.webhost.ust.hk/database/contractor/maeda.htm |publisher=[[Hong Kong University of Science and Technology]] |accessdate=29 February 2020}}</ref>, it opened in August 2002. The name of the station is taken from the nearby Po Lam Road North.\n\n== Station layout ==\n{|border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=3\n| rowspan=\"4\" style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray; border-top:solid 1px gray; vertical-align:top;width:50px;\"|'''U1'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border-top:solid 1px gray; border-bottom:solid 1px gray; vertical-align:top;width:100px;\"|Footbridge<br>(Exit A1, B2)\n|style=\"border-top:solid 1px gray; vertical-align:top;width:500px;\"|[[Metro City (Hong Kong)|Metro City Phases 1 and 3]]\n|-\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\"|[[Vending machines]], [[ATMs]], MTR Shops\n|-\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\"|Footbridge<br>(Exit A2, B1)\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\"|[[Metro City (Hong Kong)|Metro City Phase 2]], Transport interchange, Footbridges to [[Public housing estates in Tseung Kwan O#Po Lam Estate|Po Lam Estate]], [[Public housing estates in Tseung Kwan O#Po Lam Estate|Yan Ming Court]]\n|-\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\"|Footbridge<br>(Exit B3)\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\"|Footbridges to rooftop garden, [[The Pinnacle, Hong Kong|The Pinnacle]], [[Public_housing estates in Tseung Kwan O#King Lam Estate|King Lam Estate]]<br />[[List of libraries in Hong Kong|Tseung Kwan O Public Library]], Tseung Kwan O Swimming Pool\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray; vertical-align:top;\"|'''G<br>Concourse/<br>Platforms'''\n|Platform <span style=\"color:#{{rcr|MTR|Tseung Kwan O}};\">'''1'''</span>\n| {{rcb|MTR|Tseung Kwan O|yes}} towards [[North Point station|North Point]] or [[LOHAS Park station|LOHAS Park]] <small>([[Hang Hau Station|Hang Hau]])</small> \u2192\n|-\n|style=\"border-top:solid 2px black;border-right:solid 2px black;border-left:solid 2px black;border-bottom:solid 1px gray;text-align:center;\" colspan=2|<small>[[Side platform]], doors will open on the left</small>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray; vertical-align:top;\"|Concourse\n|Exit C, Customer service, MTR Shops\n|-\n|Vending machines\n|-\n|style=\"border-bottom:solid 1px gray;\"|[[Octopus card]] promotion machines\n|}\n[[File: MTR TKL Opening Commemoration Plaque.JPG |right|thumb|250px|Commemorative plague for the opening of [[Tseung Kwan O Line]] is at Po Lam station]]\n[[File:Po Lam Station 2013.JPG|thumb|right|250px|The concourse in 2013]]\n[[File:Po Lam MTR Station Exit A.JPG|thumb|right|250px|Exit A in 2006]]\n[[File:Po Lam Station 2013 08 part2.JPG|thumb|right|250px|Exit B in 2013]]\n[[File:Po Lam Station 2014 03 part2.JPG|thumb|right|250px|Exit C in 2014]]\n\nUnlike most [[MTR]] [[train station|stations]] and unique in the [[Tseung Kwan O Line]], the concourse, gates and platform of Po Lam station are on the same level. [[Track (rail transport)|Tracks]] ascend from underground to ground level at the southern end of the station, along [[Public_housing estates in Tseung Kwan O#King Lam Estate|King Lam Estate]]. A park is located on top of the tracks to cover them.\n\n=== Platforms ===\nThere is only one [[side platform]] (Platform 1) from which trains depart, in the same direction as they arrive. Trains, as a result, halt on their way from [[Hang Hau station]] for another train to depart at the station. Trains also stay here for a shorter period before departing than at other MTR [[Train station#Terminus|terminals]]. The single-track design (and the consequent longer train turnback time) limits the maximum train service frequency of the Tseung Kwan O Line.<ref name=layout/><ref>{{cite web|title=Supplementary Information on Tseung Kwan O Extension (Phase II) Service|url=http://www.legco.gov.hk/yr08-09/english/panels/tp/papers/tp0424cb1-2364-1-e.pdf|publisher=[[Legislative Council of Hong Kong|Legislative Council Panel on Transport]]|format=PDF|date=July 2009|accessdate=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nAcross from the platform and north of the point where the tracks merge to one, there is a [[siding (rail)|siding]] that splits from the running line for parking trains. Trains cannot access the platform from the siding, nor can they access the siding from the platform.<ref>{{cite web |title=MTR Track Diagram |url=http://mtr.hk365day.com/Railway/Special/track/MTR_track_diagram_full.pdf |website=mtr.hk365day.com |accessdate=3 March 2020 |format=PDF |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303165205/http://mtr.hk365day.com/Railway/Special/track/MTR_track_diagram_full.pdf |archivedate=3 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Po Lam Station 2017 07 part3.jpg|center|thumb|800px|<center>Platform 1 in July 2017</center>]]\n[[File: Po Lam Station 2017 part2.jpg |center|thumb|800px|<center>The concourse in August 2017</center>]]\n\n== Entrances/exits ==\nThe main exit is on Mau Yip Road, where five pedestrian [[footbridges]] link the station to a public transport interchange, shopping malls and residential buildings. There is direct access to [[Metro City (Hong Kong)|Metro City]] and [[The Pinnacle, Hong Kong|The Pinnacle]] from the concourse. Another footbridge crosses Po Fung Road and leads to [[Public housing estates in Tseung Kwan O#Po Lam Estate|Po Lam Estate]], [[Public housing estates in Tseung Kwan O#Yan Ming Court|Yan Ming Court]] and [[Public housing estates in Tseung Kwan O#Verbena Heights|Verbena Heights]].\n*'''A1''': [[Metro City (Hong Kong)#Shopping centre|Metro City Plaza III]] {{access icon|15px|Wheelchair user access}}\n*'''A2''': [[Metro City (Hong Kong)#Shopping centre|Metro City Plaza II]] {{access icon|15px|Wheelchair user access}}\n*'''B1''': [[Metro City (Hong Kong)#Shopping centre|Metro City Plaza II]]\n*'''B2''': [[Metro City (Hong Kong)#Shopping centre|Metro City Plaza I]]\n*'''B3''': [[Public_housing estates in Tseung Kwan O#King Lam Estate|King Lam Estate]]\n*'''C''': Mau Yip Road {{access icon|15px|Wheelchair user access}}\n\n== Station artwork ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! !!Name!!Artist!!Location!!Completion date\n|-\n|[[File:POA Station art.jpg|200px]]||City of Towers||Kacey Wong||Entrance A1 & B2||August 2002\n|}<ref>{{cite web |title=Art in station architecture: City of Towers |url=http://www.mtr.com.hk/en/customer/community/art_archi_city_of_towers.html |publisher=MTR Corporation |accessdate=6 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Transport connections ==\n=== Minibus routes ===\n<ref name = streetmap>{{cite web |title=Po Lam station street map |url=https://www.mtr.com.hk/archive/en/services/maps/poa.pdf |publisher=MTR Corporation |accessdate=6 March 2020 |format=PDF |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306142158/https://www.mtr.com.hk/archive/en/services/maps/poa.pdf |archivedate=6 March 2020}}</ref>\n* '''10M''' (Exit C): to [[Kwun Tong]]\n* '''11S''' (Exit A2): to [[Choi Hung Estate]] (overnight only)\n* '''12''' (Exit A2): to [[Sai Kung Town|Sai Kung]]\n* '''15''' (Exit A2): to [[Public housing estates in Tseung Kwan O#Hong Sing Garden|Hong Sing Garden]]\n* '''15A''' (Exit C): to [[Hang Hau]] (non-rush hours only)\n*